{
  "stem": "2718.1",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 12.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "Like they have a different lifestyle here.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "Which again, here it doesn't mean that-- I'm very close-- I'm very close to the issue.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "I'm very close Rabbi [?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "Feldman. ?] And I support the yeshiva as much as I can because I realize the work they're doing.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "So-- so much for a-- If that is-- if that is a question you asked, I hope-- I hope I gave you some sort of information which would be satisfactory.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Again, it is different-- synagogues, most of the synagogues in Hungary, because there were not so many of them like here, didn't have specific names.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "In the Western world, every synagogue has got a name.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There's a temple or a synagogue whatever, it's got a name.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "In Hungary, there was-- there was a township.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And it was the synagogue of that particular township.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "In Budapest, yes, there was.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "For example, you take the biggest synagogue in Hungary, and probably in Europe, which is called the Dohany utcai, which is today-- I believe everybody's flocking there to see.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "It was the most beautiful synagogue.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But our synagogue was about half an hour walk away, which was called the [INAUDIBLE] synagogue.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "It's a hard word to-- it's a hard word to understand, but whoever would listen to it ever, to our interview, here to this film, and will hear the word, will also know exactly what-- which synagogue I'm referring to.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "It was a big synagogue.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "It seated about 1,500 to 1,800 people.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah, well, to be quite specific, as far as my schooling was concerned, the first-- my first year of schooling, I went to cheder.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But for some reason or another I didn't-- I didn't sort of didn't fit into the cheder.",
      "word_count": 17
    }
  ],
